<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Jinheim</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Kilt-Wearing Freak!<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Apr 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>How did you decide that HP was better than FT?  You need a balance of course, but FT is very nice and should be a top priority.  I've got FT10 and I love it.  It noticeable increases your mana regen, which means you don't have to canni so much.<br />
<br />
As for mana... Mana is nice.  It is nice to be able to fire off a lot of blast heals without having to stop and canni.  Due to cannibalize, we do really well in healing over a long period of time, but if the **** hits the fan and you don't have time to cast kraggs or quiescence, you're going to want a nice mana pool.<br />
<br />
I'm at about 3k hp, 4k mana, and FT10, and it is perfect for my playstyle.  The focus of that statement is "MY PLAYSTYLE."  Asking questions like "how much mana should you have?" is really really pointless.  I don't understand how you think we are supposed to answer this question for you.  Just PLAY THE GAME and you will get a feel for what you need more of.  Right now I do not feel that I am lacking in any particular area, except focus effects.  I need more of those, but my numerical stats are perfectly balanced - I just need more of all of them.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
