	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Heh, nah I actually meant unbuffed.  But when I say most scenarios I mean just about anything under the sun, meaning u dont need to be full hps to supercan, can have just lost agro from a mob that hits for 1k+, etc heh.  Realize that if u have to wait to be full health to supercan, every tick u have to wait u are losing ~ FT30 because ure next supercan will refresh that much later.  Being able to supercan at basically anytime is really key and makes a large difference in ure ability to function.<br />
<br />
Certainly depending on ure situation some of these scenarios might not apply to u and u could have less hps and still have it work out for u most of the time.  For example if ure not in a raiding guild, or perhaps not doing PoP raids, etc.  When I say 3500+ I mean from an overall perspective, at that point ure able to tackle just about anything in the game and all stats like focus effects, regen, ft, hps, resists, manapool, etc are important.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Chatraz<br />
